author: City News Service
title: President Obama Scheduled To Leave San Diego Monday Afternoon
text:
President Obama Scheduled To Leave San Diego Monday Afternoon Monday, October 12, 2015 By City News Service Credit: Associated Press President Barack Obama waves as he steps out of Air Force One at Marine Corps Air Station Miramar in San Diego, Oct. 10, 2015. 
President Barack Obama is scheduled to leave San Diego Monday afternoon following a short rest at the end of a West Coast swing. 
The president flew into San Diego Saturday night after traveling to Roseburg, Oregon , the site of last week's shooting at Umpqua Community College in which nine people were killed and nine others wounded. He also stopped in San Francisco and Los Angeles for political fundraisers. 
The president spent Saturday night and Sunday relaxing with his family in Rancho Santa Fe and did not attend any public events locally. 
The president's last San Diego visit was in May 2014, when he attended a fundraiser at the home of former Qualcomm co-founder Irwin Jacobs.
